<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-09T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-09T12:36:00-05:00" n="950" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d950">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13729.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-09T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1914, 11 a.m. No.
                                2</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Carranza has issued another manifesto disowning the Convention and its
                            proceedings, calling on all proxies to retire from the Convention at or
                            before 6 p.m. of the 10th to report to principals, and on all generals
                            personally in attendance to retire at the same time and take immediate
                            charge of their commands; otherwise, the officer next in grade to assume
                            command and hold election to select successor to the disobedient
                            general. All government officials and employees are reminded that the
                            acts of the Convention are disowned and that no orders are to be obeyed
                            except those from the First Chief.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>